64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This =
past week has been a nice reminder that while America has its issues, the s=
ystem is actually pretty robust against bad actors. </p><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><=
span>On Wednesday, U.S. District Judge Jacqueline Scott Corley ruled agains=
t the FTC in its attempt to block Microsoft&#8217;s acquisition of Activisi=
on. Ben Thompson has a good breakdown </span><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck=
=2Ecom/redirect/01331568-f4ba-4788-bdc=
b-1af34ba1b7ab?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.g=
b8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64,=
 64); text-decoration: underline;">here</a><span>, which he concluded with:=
 &#8220;It is, I would grant, problematic to have a regulator that is too p=
ermissive; it&#8217;s worse, though, to have one that is so ideological tha=
t every opinion against it is embarrassing in the totality of its dismissiv=
eness.&#8221; </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.c=
om/redirect/6d6504c1-41bc-466e-b0ff-6283af17a17f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8=
J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); text-decoration: underline;">The Wall Street Journal Editorial Board</a=
><span> was even more blunt about Khan: &#8220;Yet this is Ms. Khan&#8217;s=
 method: Sue first based on dubious or long-repudiated antitrust legal theo=
ries, then scramble to find evidence to support the agency&#8217;s claims. =
A CEO with her record of failure would be out of a job.&#8221;</span></p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">If that approach sounds familiar, it&#8217;s because it&#82=
17;s similar to the one Gensler has been taking to crypto at the SEC: enfor=
ce first, make rules later. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And in another bit =
of </span><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/8e2ef8ab-4148-4189-84=
8e-57a443f9ded7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">=
great news</a><span> for innovation, &#8220;U.S. District Judge Analisa Tor=
res agreed with Ripple Labs&#8217; argument that roughly half of its sales =
of XRP didn&#8217;t violate investor-protection laws.&#8221; The XRP tokens=
 Ripple sold directly to institutional investors were securities, which Rip=
ple should have registered, and the company faces penalties for not doing s=
o. Importantly, however, the XRP tokens Ripple sold through exchanges were =
</span><em><strong>not</strong></em><span> securities offerings, implying t=
hat cryptocurrencies listed on exchanges aren&#8217;t necessarily securitie=
s, no matter how they were originally sold. </span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I&=
#8217;m not a particularly big fan of Ripple, but I am a fan of the precede=
nt the case sets for good projects in crypto. There&#8217;s a little more c=
larity. Plus, the XRP case &#8212; which a lawyer friend told me could not =
have had a worse set of facts for Ripple &#8212; should set the tone for up=
coming SEC legal battles against crypto, including the big one against Coin=
base. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Lest we get too excited, the battles are =
still ongoing. The order in the Ripple case is &#8220;</span><a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.sbstck.com/redirect/881161a9-727a-495a-839e-868c2dc42b6a?j=3DeyJ1=
IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">just a partial summary j=
udgment from a single district court judge</a><span>.&#8221; The Coinbase c=
ase is still to come. Khan will appeal the Microsoft/Activision decision. T=
he FTC has ongoing investigations of all of the big tech companies, includi=
ng a </span><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/8d9e193b-46be-438c-=
95c6-1650b9bd779e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;=
">fresh one into OpenAI</a><span>, and the SEC would like to continue to tr=
y to sue crypto out of existence. It&#8217;s too early for victory laps. Th=
at said, it&#8217;s great to see those checks and balances you learned abou=
t in 5th Grade Social Studies class in action. </span></p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
><span>Regulation and enforcement are important and healthy. </span><a href=
=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/69a59aa2-a096-4bf5-b602-a6c0a07594ad?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Celsius CEO Alex =
Mashinsky was arrested this week</a><span>, and the crypto industry cheered=
=2E Real consumer protection, and real=20=
consequences for those who intentional=
ly harm consumers, are great things. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But abusi=
ng power to extrajudicially push through an ideological and celebrity-motiv=
ated agenda is not good, and it makes me very happy to see that, for now, i=
t&#8217;s also ineffective. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Two wannabe regfluencers =
overreached, and the American legal system slapped their hands. Entrepreneu=
rs can build with a little more confidence in the system. God Bless America=
